opendial.domains.rules.effects

Class Effect

  • java.lang.Object
    • opendial.domains.rules.effects.Effect
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Value>, Value

    public class Effect
extends java.lang.Object
implements Value
    A complex effect, represented as a combination of elementary sub-effects connected via an implicit AND relation.
    Version:
    $Date:: 2014-11-03 17:35:57 #$
    Author:
    Pierre Lison (plison@ifi.uio.no)

      • getValues

        public java.util.Set<Value> getValues(java.lang.String variable,
                                      BasicEffect.EffectType type)
        Returns the set of values specified in the effect for the given variable and effect type. The method accepts the effect types SET, DISCARD and ADD (the CLEAR effect does not return any value). If several effects are defined with distinct priorities, only the effect with highest priority is retained.
        Parameters:
        variable - the variable
        type - the effect type
        Returns:
        the values specified in the effect
